This was a restaurant that I liked so much that everything was perfect. First of all, noodles with mackerel were good because they didn't have any unique fishy taste of mackerel, and noodles with seaweed were also light and spicy, so it was even better because it was my first time eating it. It was so delicious that I ordered additional 'Ge woo sushi' as soon as I ate it, in a word, it would be said to be the taste of heaven. Personally, 'Ge woo sushi' was made by mixing intestinal abalone and cream cheese, and then wrapped in seaweed with tuna sashimi, and the taste of the abalone intestinal sauce was fantastic. The last fried tofu sushi was delicious, but there was no special feeling.
